commText: Welcome back.. Punjab Kings bring in Prabhsimran Singh as their impact sub, Arshdeep makes way. Chameera is making his debut for KKR and he's been given the new ball. There's a slip in place. We are all set to go..
Pace vs spin in this innings \nPace: 4/205 from 14 overs (ER: 14.64) \nSpin: 1/54 from 6 overs (ER: 9)
Bowlers conceding 50-plus runs in an IPL spell most often 7 - Mohit Sharma 6 - Bhuvneshwar Kumar 6 - Mohammed Shami 6 - Pat Cummins 6 - Sam Curran 6 - Kagiso Rabada

Most expensive bowling returns for PBKS 0/66 - Mujeeb Ur Rahman vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2019 1/66 - Arshdeep Singh vs MI, Mohali, 2023 1/65 - Sandeep Sharma vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2014 0/62 - Michael Neser vs RCB, Mohali, 2013 1/60 - Sam Curran vs KKR, Kolkata, 2024

Most sixes in an IPL innings for KKR 18 vs DC, Visakhapatnam, 2024 18 vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2024 17 vs CSK, Chennai, 2018 17 vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2019

250-plus team totals in the IPL 287/3 - SRH vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2024 277/3 - SRH vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 272/7 - KKR vs DC, Visakhapatnam, 2024 266/7 - SRH vs DC, Delhi, 2024 263/5 - RCB vs PWI, Bengaluru, 2013 261/6 - KKR vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2024 262/7 - RCB vs SRH, Bengaluru, 2024 257/5 - LSG vs PBKS, Mohali, 2023

21:25 Local Time, 15:55 GMT: Another IPL night, another 250+ score and another venue's highest total breached. What once was a rarity now has become the norm. The bowlers are left hapless. But Punjab Kings would look back at their fielding today and that was what has cost them - 3 drop catches inside the first 7 overs, letting off both Narine and Salt, there's no excuse for that. The KKR openers made the most of the reprieves and smashed it around, adding 138 for the opening wicket. They did not take their foot out of the accelerator pedal as every batter who came in after that kept striking the ball cleanly and took the total past 250. Rahul Chahar and Arshdeep were the two bowlers who could walk away with their heads held up while the rest were just taken apart. This is not going to be easy for Punjab Kings especially with their top order misfiring. Hopefully Bairstow clicks for them today along with the others. Back soon..

Harshal Patel to Venkatesh Iyer, out Venkatesh Iyer Run Out!! This was clearly inside the wide marker but umpire Anil Chaudhary signalled a wide. Slower ball outside off, Iyer charges down and swings through the line, misses and he looks to steal a bye, Jitesh Sharma runs up to the stumps and takes the bails off. Venkatesh Iyer run out (Jitesh Sharma) 39(23) [4s-3 6s-2]
Harshal Patel to Venkatesh Iyer, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Punjab review! What is happening here? Iyer is run-out. But umpire Anil Chaudhary has signalled a wide. Harshal and Jitesh Sharma want it to be checked. This looked like a fair delivery. "Yes, it is passing within the guideline," says the third umpire.
Harshal Patel to Venkatesh Iyer, wide, sprays the wide yorker beyond the marker, no chance for Iyer to reach that

Harshal Patel to Ramandeep Singh, byes, 1 run, another off-pace delivery and Ramandeep is early into his heave, misses and Iyer calls for a quick single, Jitesh Sharma rolls the ball and misses the stumps, Harshal then hits the target at the bowler's end but Ramandeep had made it in
Harshal Patel to Ramandeep Singh, no run, slower ball outside off, Ramandeep swings early and does not connect. KKR review for a wide call,

Harshal Patel to Ramandeep Singh, SIX, Ramandeep needs no sighters. He showed that in the last game and today comes out and nails his first ball over the rope. Full and outside off, he shuffles across and belts it down the ground. Iyer is applauding, SRK is applauding, the whole of Eden are in party mode..
Ramandeep Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshal Patel to Rinku Singh, out Caught by Ashutosh Sharma!! Excellent catch by Ashutosh. Slower ball outside off, Rinku throws his bat and could only sky it off the outer half, the ball flies behind short third and Ashutosh backtracks, keeps his eyes on the ball and takes the catch. Rinku Singh c Ashutosh Sharma b Harshal Patel 5(4) [4s-1]
Harshal Patel to Rinku Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Harshal Patel to Rinku Singh, FOUR, full toss outside off, Rinku reaches and opens the bat face, slices it fine past short third and brings up the 250
Harshal Patel [2.0-0-37-0] is back into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Venkatesh Iyer, 2 runs, low full toss on off, Iyer mistimes the loft straight down the ground and scampers back for the second
Arshdeep Singh to Rinku Singh, 1 run, very full and close to yorker length, Rinku squeezes the drive to long-off
Arshdeep Singh to Rinku Singh, no run, what was that? Rinku wanted to play the reverse scoop or paddle, but Arshdeep goes full outside off, Rinku does not bother to go through with the shot
Rinku Singh, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Arshdeep Singh to Shreyas Iyer, out Caught by Rabada!! Little pause in the carnage. Iyer perishes while looking for the maximum. Arshdeep goes full and wide outside off, makes Iyer reach for the big shot and the KKR skipper slices it to deep backward point, Rabada runs to his left and takes a good catch. Quickfire cameo from Iyer and he's done his job. Shreyas Iyer c Rabada b Arshdeep Singh 28(10) [4s-1 6s-3]
Arshdeep Singh to Shreyas Iyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Arshdeep Singh to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, very full and close to yorker range, Iyer drives to long-off

Arshdeep Singh to Venkatesh Iyer, SIX, raining sixes at the moment. Iyers carnage at Eden! Arshdeep too misses the yorker and feeds it in the slot, Iyer uses his long levers to pump it over extra cover
Arshdeep Singh [3.0-0-35-1] is back into the attack

Sam Curran to Shreyas Iyer, SIX, this is better than the previous one. In fact, every shot kept getting better and better. Curran tries to go for the wide yorker but does not quite nail it, Iyer opens the bat face and slices it over the point fence

Sam Curran to Shreyas Iyer, SIX, that's the best of the lot. Curran misses the yorker and the line is on leg-stump, Iyer clears his front leg and whips it with his bottom hand into the deep mid-wicket crowd
Sam Curran to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, full and outside off, not quite yorker range and Iyer had the room to free his arms, slams it up and over the extra cover region, one bounce and over the ropes
Sam Curran to Shreyas Iyer, SIX, goes short but the ball just sits up for Iyer to be smashed, he throws everything behind the pull and nails it over deep square leg
Sam Curran to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, full pitcher outside off, Iyer drills it straight to long-off
Sam Curran to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, I0$ yorker at the stumps, Iyer clears his front leg and digs it to mid-off
Sam Curran [3.0-0-36-1] is back into the attack
Rabada to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, off-pace delivery bowled into the wicket, Iyer mistimes the pull in front of deep square leg
Rabada to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, in the air and safe. Short ball and Iyer is rushed on the pull, he gets a top-edge and the ball lands over backward square leg
Rabada to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, I0$ fullish delivery, Iyer is through the drive early and cue-ends it to mid-off
Rabada to Venkatesh Iyer, FOUR, on a length and outside off, Iyer had the width and he smashes it over the extra cover region
STAT: 200-plus totals have now been registered in seven of the nine innings at the Eden Gardens this IPL.
Rabada to Venkatesh Iyer, 2 runs, charges down and is met by a slower ball, checks the pull shot and the ball goes in front of square, two more
Rabada to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, I0$ back of a length delivery, Iyer lofts on the rise and mistimes it, lands in front of sweeper cover
Kagiso Rabada [2.0-0-43-0] is back into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, I0$ low full toss outside off, Iyer toe-ends it back to Arshdeep
Arshdeep Singh to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, I0$ short and bowled into the wicket, Iyer pulls to deep mid-wicket
Arshdeep Singh to Shreyas Iyer, 2 runs, short of length angled across, Iyer rides the bounce and punches it behind square on the off-side
Shreyas Iyer, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Arshdeep Singh to Russell, out Caught by Harshal Patel!! The drop does not cost much. Arshdeep has a big wicket for Punjab. He went short and into the wicket, got nice height on the delivery and Russell was ducking, but decides to play the hook and is in no position to get it off the middle. In the end, it looked like he was just trying to swat it away and the top-edge went straight up, Harshal settles near square leg and makes no mistake. Russell c Harshal Patel b Arshdeep Singh 24(12) [4s-2 6s-2]
Arshdeep Singh to Russell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Arshdeep Singh to Russell, FOUR, dropped! Tough chance and Jitesh Sharma parries it away. Full and slanted outside off, Russell throws his bat and the outside edge flies to the right of the keeper, Jitesh dives and palms it past short third. Could have left it to the short third fielder? The fielder was fine and pretty close as well
Arshdeep Singh to Russell, wide, once more Arshdeep flings the wide yorker beyond the marker, Russell ignores this time
Arshdeep Singh to Russell, wide, tries to keep it away from Russell's range and sprays it outside off, Russell can't reach that
There's a straight long-off in place

Arshdeep Singh to Russell, SIX, smashed! This ball was only struck 13 meters high. Flat six! Arshdeep misses the yorker and Russell does not need a second invitation, he thumps it straight down the ground
Most sixes for KKR in the IPL 201 - Andre Russell 106 - Nitish Rana 88 - Sunil Narine 85 - Yusuf Pathan 85 - Robin Uthappa

Arshdeep Singh to Russell, wide, full and angled outside off, Russell throws the kitchen sink and does not connect. Arshdeep checks with Jitesh Sharma should they review for wide. The timer runs out and the review does not come
Arshdeep Singh [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Over Summary (11-15): -- Narine falls to Chahar for 71 -- Salt smashes two sixes off Curran and then falls to him for 75 -- Brar taken down by Russell and Iyer

Harpreet Brar to Venkatesh Iyer, SIX, finally Iyer comes to the party. This was in the slot and he could hardly miss, just extends his arms and lofts through the line to send the ball sailing over long-on
Harpreet Brar to Russell, 1 run, slows it up outside off, Russell goes hard on the big shot and mistimes it to long-off
Harpreet Brar to Russell, no run, arm-ball around off, Russell chops it towards point. He had to get his bat down in a hurried manner
Harpreet Brar to Russell, SIX, fraction short and Russell is quick to pounce, he rocks back and pummels the pull over deep mid-wicket
Harpreet Brar to Russell, no run, fired full and at the stumps, Russell drives uppishly but just short of cover, good stop by Ashutosh
Harpreet Brar to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, comes down the track and works it to long-on
Harpreet Brar [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack

Rahul Chahar to Russell, no run, short and outside off, Russell cuts to cover and Ashutosh makes the stop, he then throws it wide of Jitesh Sharma and the pair take the single. But umpire Anil Chaudhary signals the ball was dead and the single does not count
Rahul Chahar to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, googly outside off, Iyer drags the pull to deep mid-wicket
Rahul Chahar to Russell, 1 run, shortens the length to Russell and he tucks it backward of square leg
Rahul Chahar to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, wrong 'un outside off, Iyer chops it square and settles with a single
Rahul Chahar to Venkatesh Iyer, FOUR, flatter delivery around off, Iyer sits down and sweeps behind square on the leg-side, beating the fielder in the deep
Rahul Chahar to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, googly outside off, Iyer pushes off the outer half to backward point and wants a single. Russell sends him back
Rahul Chahar [3.0-0-26-1] is back into the attack

Time for the strategic break. PBKS have managed to dismiss both openers, but it was only after they smashed them to smithereens. Russell is in and KKR will be very disappointed if they fall short of 250 from here

Highest run-rates for a 100-plus opening stand in the IPL 20.68 - 131 off 38 - Travis Head & Abhishek Sharma (SRH) vs DC, Delhi, 2024 17.02 - 105 off 37 - Chris Lynn & Sunil Narine (KKR) vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2017 14.86 - 109 off 44 - Brendon McCullum & Dwayne Smith (CSK) vs MI, Mumbai WS, 2015 13.36 - 147 off 66 - Chris Gayle & Virat Kohli (RCB) vs PBKS, Bengaluru, 2016 13.35 - 138 off 62 - Sunil Narine & Phil Salt (KKR) vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2024
Sam Curran to Russell, 2 runs, low full-toss on the pads, clipped in front of square on the on-side and Russell comes back for the second
Sam Curran to Russell, FOUR, nicely played, banged in short by Curran - but Russell arches back slightly and then plays the upper-cut, went fdine and to the ropes on the bounce
Sunil Narine as an opener vs PBKS Inns: 6 Runs: 226 Avg: 37.66 SR: 207.33 50s: 2 HS: 75 4s/6s: 27/14
Sam Curran to Russell, no run, fuller length delivery at the stumps, pushed back at the bowler with a straight bat
Andre Russell, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sam Curran to Philip Salt, out Bowled!! Curran has his man now, but it has come at quite a cost - the perfect yorker, full and straight, Salt was staying deep in the crease, swipes all-around and loses his off-stump. Salt walks off to a loud ovation, but a bigger one awaits as Russell makes his way to the playing arena. Philip Salt b Sam Curran 75(37) [4s-6 6s-6]
Sam Curran to Philip Salt, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Sam Curran to Philip Salt, SIX, this is poor from Curran - attempts the slower ball, but it's too full and too wide of off, lets Salt free his rams as he clatters it over long-off for another maximum
Sam Curran to Philip Salt, SIX, hammered, a loopy slower ball from Curran, Salt gets forward and then thumps it straight of long-off, no chance for Bairstow
Sam Curran [2.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack

Highest partnerships for KKR in the IPL (any wicket) 184* - Gautam Gambhir & Chris Lynn vs GL, Rajkot, 2017 158 - Gautam Gambhir & Robin Uthappa vs RPS, Pune, 2017 152* - Gautam Gambhir & Jacques Kallis vs RR, Jaipur, 2011 138 - Sunil Narine & Phil Salt vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2024 136 - Manvinder Bisla & Jacques Kallis vs CSK, Chennai, 2012 final The 138-run partnership between Narine and Salt was the 8th 100-plus opening stand for KKR in the IPL, and the first since 105 between Narine and Lynn against RCB in Bengaluru back in 2017.

Harpreet Brar to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, very full and on off, Venkatesh jammed the bat hard and the ball lobbed back at the bowler - Jitesh Sharma is interested in an appeal, but it's bounced off the pitch and the appeal dies down
Harpreet Brar to Philip Salt, 1 run, flighted delivery outside off, punched to the left of cover who dives over and makes a half-stop
Harpreet Brar to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, pushed through outside off, hacked down to long-on for a single

Harpreet Brar to Venkatesh Iyer, 2 runs, a big top-edge and Venkatesh gets lucky, was shaping for the big slog-sweep, angled across and he couldn't get on top of the bounce, spoons it back over the bowler's head
Harpreet Brar to Venkatesh Iyer, 2 runs, Venkatesh shimmies down the pitch to a well flighted delivery and then places the drive to the left of long-on, comes back for the second
Harpreet Brar to Philip Salt, 1 run, flighted delivery well wide of off, driven past cover for a single
Harpreet Brar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Philip Salt, 1 run, dropped short and wide of off, Salt has to reach out and slaps a one-handed cut through cover
Rahul Chahar to Venkatesh Iyer, leg byes, 1 run, tossed up on the pads, past Venkatesh's flick and rolls to the left of short fine for a leg-bye

Highest scores after first 10 overs of an IPL innings 158/4 - SRH vs DC, Delhi, 2024 148/2 - SRH vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 141/2 - MI vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2024 138/4 - DC vs SRH, Delhi, 2024 137/0 - KKR vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2024 135/1 - KKR vs DC, Visakhapatnam, 2024
Rahul Chahar to Venkatesh Iyer, FOUR, nicely played, flighted delivery just outside off - Venkatesh brings out the reverse sweep and gets it fine, beating short third man and runs away to the ropes

Rahul Chahar to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, beautifully bowled, the leg-break from Chahar - drifts away and then spins back, goes through the gat as Venkatesh pushed forward and he's lucky that it didn't hit the off-stump
Venkatesh Iyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Rahul Chahar to Narine, out Caught by Bairstow!! Finally, a catch has been taken and Narine has been dismissed. The wrong 'un from Chahar, pushed across the left-hander - Narine couldn't get on top of the bounce as he swivelled on the pull, clonked it off the bottom of the bat and it's a simple catch to Bairstow, at long-on. Narine c Bairstow b Rahul Chahar 71(32) [4s-9 6s-4]
Rahul Chahar to Narine, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Rahul Chahar to Philip Salt, 1 run, the round the wicket action from Chahar - flighted delivery outside off and it's driven down to long-off for a single

Over Summary (6-10): -- Salt is dropped by Curran -- Chahar is miffed as Salt gets another chance and this time Rabada drops him -- Rabada goes for 22 in his second over -- Narine smashes another fifty -- Narine survives an LBW scare thanks to DRS after being given out -- Salt reaches his fifty in style as well

Harshal Patel to Philip Salt, 1 run, fuller length delivery and well wide of off - Salt shuffles across and then toe-ends the lofted drive, the fielder at long-off doesn't go for the catch and is happy to collect it on the bounce, 19 off the over
Harshal Patel to Philip Salt, no ball, Harshal looks to bowl the wide yorker, but he's puished it past the cut strip, called as a no-ball and Salt will get a free-hit

Harshal Patel to Philip Salt, SIX, Salt is rubbing salt into PBKS's wounds now - on a good length and at the stumps, he swings through the line, the connection is clean and the ball soars over the ropes at long-on
Harshal Patel to Narine, 1 run, on a good length and well wide of off, Narine moves across and drags it off the inner half, bounces down to long-on
The ball has had to be replaced
Harshal Patel to Narine, SIX, clattered, length ball from Harshal, right in the slot and Narine drills it high over long-on, clears the fielder in the deep with ridiculous ease
Harshal Patel to Narine, no run, the slower yorker, wide of off and Narine can't jam it out, a rare dot ball

Harshal Patel to Narine, FOUR, this is all too easy for Narine - Harshal comes from round the wicket and pushes one full and wide of off, Narine throws his hands on the drive and slices it over backward point for another boundary
Harshal Patel [1.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Philip Salt, no run, pushed through by Chahar - Salt rocks back on the pull and gets a bottom-edge onto the thigh
Most runs in the Powerplay in IPL 2024 259 - Travis Head (SR: 229.20) 216 - Virat Kohli (SR: 155.39) 204 - Sunil Narine (SR: 177.39) 201 - Abhishek Sharma (SR: 233.72) 193 - Phil Salt (SR: 175.45)
Rahul Chahar to Philip Salt, 2 runs, tossed up well wide of off - Salt makes room and then cuts it late, places it behind square on the off-side for a couple

Rahul Chahar to Philip Salt, FOUR, cracking shot, dragged short by Chahar - Salt makes room and clatters it wide of cover, pl;enty of power and the fielder at long-off has no chance, brings up Salt's fifty
Rahul Chahar to Narine, 1 run, dropped short and wide of off, chopped down to long-off for a single

Rahul Chahar to Narine, no run, a pleading shout for LBW, it's given OUT and Narine has reviewed it immediately. No bat, but is it sliding past the off-stump? Onto ball-tracking: It has straightened, but it's bouncing over the leg-stump. A successful review and it's NOT OUT. Was the top-spinner and Narine was looking to slog it over mid-wicket, missed and was struck on the back-thigh

Rahul Chahar to Narine, SIX, massive, Narine shimmies down the pitch, was the wro9ng 'un, but he got right to the pitch of the ball and then thumped it over the bowler's head, sailed over onto the sightscreen

Highest Powerplay scores for KKR 105/0 vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2017 (Narine: 54* off 16) 88/1 vs DC, Visakhapatnam, 2024 (Narine: 52* off 21) 85/0 vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2024 (Narine: 47* off 20) 76/0 vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2024 (Narine: 38* off 15) 76/1 vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2017 (Narine: 37 off 18)

Rabada to Philip Salt, SIX, this is so easy now for KKR and Salt - lengthg ball angling into the right-hander - Salt shuffles across, gets inside the line and then flaps it over long leg for a maximum

Rabada to Philip Salt, FOUR, on a good length and angling into the right-hander, Salt uses that to his benefit, swivels across, gets inside the line and then flicks it over backward square leg, bounces away wide of the fielder in the deep
Rabada to Philip Salt, wide, the slower ball from Rabada, but he's pushed it down leg and is called as a wide
Rabada to Narine, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off - Narine shuffles across and swipes it past mid-wicket for a single
Rabada to Narine, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Narine - width on offer and he threw his hands on the cut, gets a thick edge that went flying over backward point, brings up his fifty as well

Rabada to Narine, FOUR, Rabada is leaking boundaries at the moment, on a good length and angling across the left-hander, width on offer and Narine laces the drive over cover - Rossouw comes running across, puts in the dive and can't reach out, one bounce and over the ropes
Rabada to Narine, no run, slower ball angled across the left-hander, Narine swings hard and misses
Rabada to Narine, wide, banged in short, but it sails over Narine's head and is called as a wide
Rabada to Narine, wide, Rabada attempts the slower ball, but it's too wide and past the tramlines, called as a wide
Kagiso Rabada [1.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Narine, 1 run, the wrong 'un, Narine doesn't spot it as he pushed forward, gets a thick edge through slip for a single

Rahul Chahar to Philip Salt, 1 run, another chance and Rabada has dropped it, flighted delivery from Chahar, was the leg-break, was slower and wider of off, Salt had to reach out on the drive and couldn't keep it down, went to backward point's right - Rabada moved swiftly, dived and got both hands, only to let the ball slip out
Rahul Chahar to Narine, 1 run, tossed up on the leg-stump line, Narine sweeps and gets an under-edge to short fine

Rahul Chahar to Narine, no run, appeal for LBW, but there could've been an inside edge on that, a big inside edge - Narine was shaping for the reverse sweep and smashed a thick edge onto his front-pad
Rahul Chahar to Narine, FOUR, lovely, Narine brings out the reverse sweep - bends down low, lets the ball come and then flaps it over backward point for a boundary
Rahul Chahar to Narine, no run, flighted delivery outside off, a hint of grip as Narine finds backward point with the cut
Rahul Chahar, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Rahul Chahar as Curran turns to spin
Time for the strategic break. Punjab opted to bowl and have bled runs, they did create a couple of chances - one off Narine and Salt, but they wasted it with sloppy fielding.
Arshdeep Singh to Narine, 1 run, another full-toss, Narine miscues the slog past square leg for a single

Arshdeep Singh to Philip Salt, 1 run, chance and Curran has put it down , this'll not help Punjab Kings one bit - fuller length delivery and Salt drilled the drive to mid-off, came at a rate of knots, but it came at a good height, should've taken it at this level, but Curran let the ball hit his wrists and pop out

Arshdeep Singh to Philip Salt, no run, another full-toss and Arshdeep gets away with another one - he has a packed off-side field and the aim is to go for the wide yorkers, a full-toss and Salt finds cover with the drive
Arshdeep Singh to Philip Salt, no run, a wide full-toss and Arshdeep gets away with it, Salt finding the fielder at cover-point with the drive
Arshdeep Singh to Philip Salt, no run, the wide yorker from Arshdeep - Salt was looking to jam it out and missed

Arshdeep Singh to Philip Salt, FOUR, the runs keep coming - slower ball from Arshdeep, pushed across the right-hander, Salt throws his hands on the drive, gets a thick edge and the ball sails over backward point for a boundary
Arshdeep Singh [1.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack

Over Summary (1-5): -- Narine slams Arshdeep for a sixer and a four in the second over of the game -- Harshal concedes 18 off his first over -- Rabada goes for 21 in his first over -- KKR smash 70 off 5 overs

Sam Curran to Narine, FOUR, nicely bowled, but even that goes to the ropes - almost the perfect leg-stump yorker, Narine jammed the bat down and squeezed a thick inside edge, no one behind square on the on-side and the ball runs away to the ropes
Sam Curran to Philip Salt, 1 run, back of a length and angling across the right-hander, hacked away through mid-wicket for a single
Sam Curran to Narine, 1 run, fuller length delivery on off, Narine squirts a thick inside edge on the drive to square leg
Sam Curran to Philip Salt, 1 run, Curran shortens the length and angles one across the right-hander, Salt chops hard and mistimes the drive inh front of cover-point
Sam Curran to Philip Salt, FOUR, drilled, the slower ball from Curran, but he's offered plenty of width and it's sent whistling through extra-cover, no need to run for those
Sam Curran to Philip Salt, no run, the slower cutter from Curran - angled across the right-hander and beat Salt for pace on the cut, barely carried through to Jitesh Sharma
Sam Curran [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Rabada to Narine, FOUR, 21 off the over, low full-toss as Narine tried to follow Narine - he still makes some room and then slices the drive over cover, bounces away to the ropes
Rabada to Narine, SIX, massive, back of a length and at the stumps, was the attempted slower ball, but it simply sat up to be smacked, Narine bacvks away and then hammers the pull over mid-wicket
Rabada to Narine, FOUR, the boundaries keep coming, low full-toss from Rabada and Narine has shovelled it wide of mid-on - bounces away and past the reach of the fielder at long-on
Rabada to Philip Salt, 1 run, yorker length delivery on the pads, chipped off the inner half, over square leg for a single
Rabada to Philip Salt, wide, the slower ball from Rabada, but he spills it down leg and is called as a wide
Rabada to Philip Salt, FOUR, creamed, overpitched by Rabada - Salt leans forward and then drives it through the line, over mid-off and a one-bounce boundary
Rabada to Narine, 1 run, fuller length delivery on the pads, flicked over mid-wicket - there's a fielder in the deep and it gets to him on the bounce
Kagiso Rabada, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Harshal Patel to Philip Salt, no run, much better from Harshal, but 18 off the over, was a slower yorker outside off and Salt couldn't squeeze it out
Harshal Patel to Philip Salt, SIX, crunched, it's flying sixes at the moment at the Eden - back of a length and at the stumps, Salt backs away and then swats it over mid-wicket
Harshal Patel to Philip Salt, FOUR, the pressure tells on Harshal - offers a juicy full-toss as he looked to bowl the slower ball, chipped over wide mid-on - one bounce and over the ropes

Harshal Patel to Philip Salt, SIX, clubbed, on a good length and at the stumps, was another slower ball, but it's too full from Harshal - Salt brings the bottom-hand into play as he shovelled it high over mid-wicket

Harshal Patel to Narine, 1 run, chance and Narine has been put down - back of a length and well wide of off, Narine stood tall and then dabbed it to the right of backward point. Brar dived across, got both hands and lets the ball pop out. Could be an expensive miss

Harshal Patel to Philip Salt, 1 run, a leading edge, and the ball lands wide of mid-on - was the slower ball and Salt was early into the flick, closed the face of the bat and the leading edge popped over the bowler's head
Harshal Patel, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
First change and it's Harshal Patel
Arshdeep Singh to Narine, no run, on a good length and angling across the left-hander, Narine swings hard and is beaten on the outside edge

Arshdeep Singh to Narine, FOUR, that's too easy for Narine - another attempted slower ball, but this is a loopy full-toss, he doesn't get hold of the shovel, but has enough to clear mid-on and bounces away to the ropes
Arshdeep Singh to Narine, wide, Arshdeep loses his line once again, he's looking to go wide, but he's past the tramlines once again, callled as a wide
Arshdeep Singh to Narine, wide, the slower ball from Arshdeep, but he's pushed it well wide of the tramline, called as a wide

Arshdeep Singh to Narine, SIX, smashed, fraction too short from Arshdeep - Narine spots the length early, swivels across and then thumps the pull over square leg, went sailing a long way into the crowd
Arshdeep Singh to Philip Salt, 1 run, on a good length and well wide of off, Salt toe-ends the drive to the left of mid-off for a single
The slip has been removed

Arshdeep Singh to Philip Salt, no run, Arshdeep keeps it on a length and just outside off - Salt runs down the pitch and swings hard, gets a thick inside edge that bounces off his pad and rolls past the off-stump
Arshdeep Singh to Philip Salt, no run, short of a good length and pushed across the right-hander, Salt swings across the line and misses
Arshdeep Singh, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
A wide slip for Arshdeep
Sam Curran to Narine, 2 runs, another slower ball from Curran, but he offers width and Narine throws his hands on the drive, carves it over cover and he's back for the second
Sam Curran to Narine, no run, nicely bowled, Curran bowls the slower ball around off, no pace to work with and Narine is early into the slog, beaten by a long way
Sam Curran to Narine, no run, on a good length and at the stumps, Narine backs away on the drive and meets thin air - the extra bounce meant that the ball zipped over the top of middle-stump
Sam Curran to Narine, FOUR, hammered, Narine needs no sighters - on a good length and well wide of off, Narine backs away and then flays the drive wide of cover-point, runs away to the ropes
Sam Curran to Philip Salt, 1 run, fuller length delivery and angling across the right-hander, Salt throws his hands on the drive and gets a thick edge towards third man, on the bounce to the fielder
Sam Curran to Philip Salt, no run, on a good length and at the pads, Salt shuffles across and turns it onto the on-side
Philip Salt and Narine are at the crease. Philip Salt is on strike. Sam Curran will open the attack
